For the XPCOM error, see bug 134041. I don't think it explains the
Widget disposed too early errors though.  However, since I think
the XPCOM error is blocking startup, feel free to mark this as a dup
if you don't care about the other errors ;)

The XPCOM error -2147467262 no longer crashes (though it doesn't always render its contents correctly yet).  Marking report as a duplicate of bug 133000, which captures the Widget disposed too early! problem.


*** This bug has been marked as a duplicate of 133000 ***
As a follow-up, now that the XPCOM crash is fixed (and is rendering properly as well), you should not see the Widget disposed too early! problem anymore either.
